b'Power up logistics: A unit of DHL Global Forwarding has been supporting the expansion of a lithium facility in El Salar del Hombre Muerto in the province of Catamarca, :Argentina: Argentina. With the site located at about 4,000 metres above sea level, DHL was contracted to provide numerous services, ranging from chartering and movement of over-sized cargo to personnel transfers to the site. Factors such as the extreme :thermometer_selector: weather conditions, lack of :dashing_away: oxygen and :satellite_antenna: limited telephone signal, among others, required highest health, :safety_vest: safety and environment standards and additional safety arrangements for the :construction_worker: staff. Great teamwork from a great team under tough conditions!'

b'Stay safe! #DHL employees and sustainable fashion brand @grubenhelden deliver a face mask that reveals more than it hides. Read the whole story here \xe2\x80\xa6
With COVID 19 impacting our world in more ways than ever imagined, we\xe2\x80\x99ve made it priority #1 at DHL to protect both our people and everyone around them . We\xe2\x80\x99ve had to adjust to this extraordinary situation and put the necessary changes in place.
As part of this all, we\xe2\x80\x99ve sought out dialogue with our customers like the German sustainable fashion startup Grubenhelden. Together with Grubenhelden, we came up with the idea of designing our own face mask using the same fabric as the polo shirts worn by DHL couriers worldwide.
When the first batch of red and yellow face masks were finally ready, we asked both DHL and
Grubenhelden employees to help us create a short video. The response was tremendous. And then, during the filming , something unexpected happened! Our volunteer models opened up and started talking about how the pandemic has changed their lives.
That\xe2\x80\x99s when we realized: the mask actually reveals more than it hides. The mask shows who we are on the inside and it shows us how something as small as a red and yellow mask can become a statement for more humanity and community.
Learn More: InMotion.DHL/Mask'

b'Documentary film #Honeyland - supported by DHL - is nominated for the 92nd :trophy: Oscars. \xe2\x80\x9cTake only half, leave half to nature and if one disobeys the rule, than we all suffer. I strongly believe that if we embrace these messages, our planet will be a much better place for all.\xe2\x80\x9d
- Hatidze Muratova, a wild beekeeper and the main character of the movie -

The documentary Honeyland tells the story of Hatidze who lives in an isolated mountain region deep in the Balkans with his family. The film is nominated in the categories Best Documentary Feature and Best International Feature Film, the only documentary ever to be nominated in this category. 
DHL has supported in spreading the film\xe2\x80\x99s message and deliver wild honey for a good cause by initiating the call for donations for the protagonists of the movie. The idea is that those who donate $30 USD or more, will receive a 30 gram jar of honey as a present and appreciation from Hatidze. DHL Express Macedonia is also donating \xe2\x82\xac1 for each international shipment they deliver.
Want to know more? Follow the links in our bio!
#oscarnominations #greatmovie #dhl #donation #support #savetheplanet #beekeeping'
